INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $k8s$Application Observability and Maintenance$k8s$, 3, $k8s$SINGLE$k8s$::"QType", $k8s$A readiness probe uses `periodSeconds: 5`, `successThreshold: 1`, `failureThreshold: 3`. After the Pod becomes unready, how many consecutive successful probes return it to Ready?$k8s$, $k8s$[{"id":"a","text":"1"},{"id":"b","text":"3"},{"id":"c","text":"5"},{"id":"d","text":"It never returns automatically."}]$k8s$::jsonb, $k8s$["a"]$k8s$::jsonb, $k8s$`successThreshold` for readiness defaults to 1; a single success flips the Pod back to Ready. `failureThreshold` (3) is how many failures mark it unready.$k8s$, $k8s$[{"url":"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-startup-probes/","label":"Kubernetes Docs — Liveness/Readiness/Startup Probes"}]$k8s$::jsonb, $k8s$PUBLISHED$k8s$::"QStatus", $k8s$manual:ckad-seed$k8s$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = $k8s$CKAD-P2$k8s$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $k8s$A readiness probe uses `periodSeconds: 5`, `successThreshold: 1`, `failureThreshold: 3`. After the Pod becomes unready, how many consecutive successful probes return it to Ready?$k8s$);
